==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shrapnel
<hw>Shrap"nel</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Applied as an
appellation to a kind of shell invented by Gen. H. <xex>Shrapnel</xex>
of the British army.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A shrapnel shell;
shrapnel shells, collectively.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Shrapnel shell</b></col> <fld>(Gunnery)</fld>, <cd>a
projectile for a cannon, consisting of a shell filled with bullets and a
small bursting charge to scatter them at any given point while in
flight. See the Note under <er>Case shot</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Shred</ent>⟦br⟧
